The paper deals with the design and performance evaluation of a communication system, which involves signal processing, information theory, and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, including communication theory. The paper also involves communication aspects, such as channel modeling and coding, which are covered in cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves signal processing aspects, such as waveform design and oversampling, which are covered in cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper involves aspects of modulation and demodulation, which are covered in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves aspects of hardware implementation, such as analog-to-digital conversion and filtering, which are covered in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
